parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of fuel injectors can cause the vehicle to run rough, lose power, and potentially lead to engine compartment fires, which can result in serious damage to the vehicle and pose a risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: fuel injectors leak fuel over the engine
excess fuel goes into the cylinder
and the potential for engine compartment fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Warped Brake Rotors and Calipers Causing Vibration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors and calipers can cause the steering wheel to vibrate excessively, leading to a loss of control and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Excessive shake and steering wheel vibration while brakes are applied
intermittent lock-up and acceleration of the vehicle when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Automatic Transmission Planetary Failure due to Cooler Design
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the planetary gear in the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to seize or lose power while driving, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences sudden loss of power
the vehicle seizes or stalls while driving
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.
